from typing import List
import logging
from selenium.webdriver.remote.webdriver import WebDriver

logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)



[docs]class BrowserActions:
    """
    A class for all BrowserActions that can be performed on a webpage or webdriver.
    It contains all the methods which are associated with browsers

    :class: `browseractions`
    """

    def __init__(self, driver):
        """
        Constructor of the class
        """
        self._driver: WebDriver = driver


[docs]    def get_current_url(self) -> str:
        """
        Retrieves the current url of the webpage

        :return: url (String)
        """
        current_url = self._driver.current_url
        logger.info("Current URL is %s" % current_url)
        return current_url

[docs]    def get_current_tab_name(self) -> str:
        """
        Returns the current tab's name through windows handle

        :return: tab name (String)
        """
        window_handle = self._driver.current_window_handle
        logger.debug("Current window handle is: %s" % str(window_handle))
        return window_handle

        """

[docs]    def get_number_of_tabs(self) -> int:
        """
        Returns the number of tabs currently opened

        :return: no of tabs (String)
        """
        num_tabs = len(self._driver.window_handles)
        logger.info("Number of tabs: %s" % str(num_tabs))
        return num_tabs



[docs]    def get_tab_list(self) -> List[str]:
        """
        Returns the currently opened tabs in list

        :return: list of currently opened tabs (List)
        """
        tab_list = self._driver.window_handles
        logger.debug("List of window handles %s" % str(tab_list))
        return tab_list



[docs]    def switch_to_tab_index(self, index: int):
        """
        Switch to tab using index of that tab

        :param: index : index_of the_tab (int)
        :return: None
        """
        tab_name: str = self._driver.window_handles[index]
        logger.info("About to switch to tab: ", tab_name)
        self.switch_to_tab(tab_name)
        logger.info("Switched to new tab at index: %s successfully" % str(index))



[docs]    def switch_to_tab(self, tab_name: str):
        """
        Switch to a tab using the name of the window

        :param: tab_name: name_of_window/tab (String)
        :return: None
        """
        self._driver.switch_to.window(tab_name)
        logger.info("Switched to new tab: %s" % str(tab_name))

[docs]    def close_tab_at_index(self, index: int):
        """
        Close the tab/window at a given index position

        :param index: index_of_window/tab (int)
        :return: None
        """
        self.switch_to_tab_index(index)
        self._driver.close()
        logger.info("Closed the tab at index %s" % str(index))



[docs]    def close_tab(self, name: str):
        """
        Closing the tab/window by passing the name of window/tab

        :param name: name_of_window/tab (String)
        :return: None
        """
        self.switch_to_tab(name)

        logger.info("Closed the tab: %s" % str(name))

[docs]    def go_to_protected_url(self, full_url: str, username: str, password: str):
        """
        Opening the protected url page.

        :param full_url: url_of_the_page (String)
        :param username: username_to_login (String)
        :param password: password_to_login (String)
        :return: None
        """
        https = "https://"
        http = "http://"

        protocol = ""
        if full_url.startswith(https):
            protocol = https
        elif full_url.startswith(http):
            protocol = http

        url = full_url
        if protocol:
            url = full_url.replace(protocol, "")

        self._driver.get(f'{protocol}{username}:{password}@{url}')
